<div class="demo-content">
  <h1>ActiveAdmin Dropdown Accessibility Patch</h1>
  
  <p>This demo shows two different approaches to accessible dropdown menus:</p>
  
  <div style="margin: 2rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: #e3f2fd; border-radius: 4px;">
    <h2>Test Pages</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="/">Home Page</a></strong> - Custom accessible dropdown implementation</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/home/activeadmin_test">ActiveAdmin Test</a></strong> - Simulates ActiveAdmin's dropdown structure with the accessibility patch</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  
  <h2>ActiveAdmin Patch Files</h2>
  
  <p>The following files are ready to be applied to your ActiveAdmin application:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>JavaScript Patch:</strong> <code>app/assets/javascripts/activeadmin-dropdown-patch.js</code></li>
    <li><strong>CSS Patch:</strong> <code>app/assets/stylesheets/activeadmin-dropdown-patch.css</code></li>
  </ul>
  
  <h2>Installation Instructions</h2>
  
  <p>To apply this patch to your ActiveAdmin application:</p>
  
  <ol>
    <li>Copy the JavaScript patch to your ActiveAdmin's <code>app/assets/javascripts/active_admin.js</code></li>
    <li>Copy the CSS patch to your ActiveAdmin's <code>app/assets/stylesheets/active_admin.scss</code></li>
    <li>Restart your Rails server</li>
    <li>Test the dropdown menus with keyboard navigation</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Keyboard Navigation:</strong> Full arrow key navigation through menu items</li>
    <li><strong>Tab Support:</strong> Menu items are properly tabbable when dropdown is open</li>
    <li><strong>ARIA Attributes:</strong> Proper accessibility attributes for screen readers</li>
    <li><strong>Focus Management:</strong> Automatic focus management when opening/closing dropdowns</li>
    <li><strong>508 Compliance:</strong> Meets Section 508 accessibility requirements</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h2>Testing Instructions</h2>
  
  <p>Test both pages using only the keyboard:</p>
  
  <ol>
    <li>Use Tab to navigate to dropdown triggers</li>
    <li>Press Enter or Space to open dropdowns</li>
    <li>Use Arrow Up/Down to navigate menu items</li>
    <li>Use Home/End to jump to first/last items</li>
    <li>Press Escape to close dropdowns</li>
    <li>Use Tab to close dropdown and move to next element</li>
  </ol>
  
  <div style="margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1rem; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 4px;">
    <h3>Additional Test Area</h3>
    <p>This area is here to test tab navigation after the dropdown. Try tabbing through the page to ensure proper focus management.</p>
    <button>Test Button 1</button>
    <button>Test Button 2</button>
    <a href="#">Test Link</a>
  </div>
</div>
